	<VARIANT name="Milan" version="1.0">
		<DESCRIPTION><![CDATA[
		The Milan variant was created to strengthen Italy, providing an attacking
		rather than a defensive power. The standard rules apply; only map modifications
		have been made.
		<p>
		The map is altered creating the province of Milan between the former
		provinces of Piedmont and Venice. The supply center formerly in Venice
		is moved to Milan.
		</p>
		<p>
		The former Piedmont, which loses its contact with Tyrolia to Milan,
		is now extended northwest to offer access to Burgandy as well as
		Marseilles. To reflect these changes, it is renamed Savoy.
		</p>
		<p>
		Venice is renamed to Venetia, following the convention that only
		home supply centers have city names.
		</p>
		<p style="margin-top:21pt;">
			Author: John Norris<br>
			Electronic map by Joe Compbell and Zach DelProposto
		</p>]]></DESCRIPTION> 
